The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, January 16, 2004 				 Bharti offer for Hexacom stake off
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, Jan. 15: Bharti Tele-Venture has taken back its offer to buy Canadian TIWs 27.5 per cent stake in Hexacom as one of the shareholders has exercised the first right of refusal. 																								The companys (Bharti) offer to Telesystem International Wireless (TIW) for its 27.5 per cent stake stands terminated, Bharti informed the bourses.																								Bharti said this is because one of the two major shareholders have exercised the right of first refusal and offered to acquire the stake. Bharti, however, did not divulge the name of the shareholder who had offered to buy the stake.																								Bharti Tele-Venture had earlier entered into an agreement with TIW for purchase of the stake at Rs 102 crore. Among the two other partners while Shyam Telecom controls a 40 per cent stake, Telecom Consultant India holds a 30 per cent stake. Another Kuwait-based investor holds over 2 per cent. 
